ppunctuations.ppunctuation:
Executed: not quite regularly.
Usage: not always logical.
Dividers:
I. Colon.
II. Four dot asterisk (e.g. fols.: 3ra, l.14; 3rb, l.13; 15rb, l.5; 22rb, ls. 6, 12; 29rb, l.12); 
four dot asterisk composed of black and red dots (e.g. fols.: 5vb, ls. 5,6,7; 20ra, ls. 2,5,6,9,11,14, 15, 19, 20, 21; throughout fol. 46va);
nine dot asterisk (used throughout the text);
doubled four dot asterisks (esp. fol. 41ra, l.2);
doubled nine dots asterisks (esp. fol. 46va, l.13);
three nine dots asterisks (esp. fol. 47vb, l.4).
III. Crude ornamental band composed of two chains of black and red dots with with red zigzag line in between (esp. fols.  46va, ls.14-15, 47vb, ls. 5-6).

rubrications.rubrication:
Nomina sacra; 
four lines in both columns of the incipit page (fol. 3r), divided into two groups, alternating with black lines;
some groups of lines in fols. 8rb (ls. 15-16), 15va (ls. 13-15), 18ra (ls. 13-16), 20vb (ls. 4-6), 21ra (ls. 3-4), 22ra (ls. 5-8), 22rb (ls. 4-6, 13-14), 29ra (ls. 8-11, 16-17), 30ra (ls. 5-6, 8), 31vb (ls. 12-14), 35vb (ls. 6-7, 9-12), 38rb (ls. 4-6), 38va (ls. 10-12, 14-16), 39rb (ls. 6-7), 40va (ls. 11-12), 41ra (ls. 3-5);
the horizontal dashes above and below Ethiopic numbers; 
elements of the punctuation signs;
the words “sänbät”, “sänbätä krәstiyan qәddәst”, “sälam”;
the incipit lines (1-3) of the each strophe within text II;
names of donors; 
Additio II (fols. 47vb, l.7 – 48ra, l.8).

txquiremarks.txquiremark:
Quire  marks are written in the upper margin of fols.
fol. 11r: ፪ “2”; 
fol. 14r: ፫ “3”; 
fol. 27r: ፬ “4”;
fol. 35r: ፭ “5”.
